text: Georgia Marie Stanway (born 3 January 1999), is a professional football player from England. She plays as an attacking midfielder for Bayern Munich, a team in the Frauen-Bundesliga league, and she represents the England national football team. In 2016, she was a nominee for the BBC Young Sports Personality of the Year award, and in 2017, she was also nominated for the PFA Women's Young Player of the Year award. In June 2018, she was chosen to be part of the UEFA Women's Champions League squad of the season. In 2019, she received the PFA Women's Young Player of the Year award. == References == Category:1999 births Category:Living people Category:English footballers Category:Female footballers
